{
  "text": "The puromycin-linker was prepared according to Kurz et al. [CITATION_1] and biotinylated by carbamate bond formation between the puromycin amino group (50 \u00b5M) and the photo-cleavable biotin-reagent [CITATION_2] (NHS-PC-Biotin, 5 mM, EZ-Link TM -Biotin, Pierce Chemicals) in 25% DMSO/water for 2 h at room temperature followed by NaCl/EtOH precipitation. Photo-cleavage of the 1-(2-nitrophenyl)ethyl carbamate moiety restored the primary amino group on the 3'-terminal puromycin which acts as the peptidyl-acceptor in the fusion formation process (see Fig. 1 ).",
  "citation_candidates": [
